message.content:
Analysis of the Target Image

• Block Count and Layers  
  – There are four total blocks.  
  – They form three vertical “layers”:  
    1. A single yellow rectangular block on the bottom  
    2. Two red half‐cylinder blocks side by side in the middle (together creating the circular opening)  
    3. A single yellow rectangular block on top  

• Spatial Relationships  
  – The bottom and top layers are each one long yellow block lying horizontally.  
  – Between them, two red pieces meet in the center to form a circular hole.  

Required Blocks from the Dictionary

• Red Center Ring:  
  – Use block #7 and block #8 (each provides a “half‐tube” that together form the circular opening).  
• Yellow Top and Bottom:  
  – Use block #9 for both the bottom and the top (the same index can be reused, as shown in the dictionary).  

Assembly Instructions

{
  Step1: Move block with index 9    // Place bottom yellow bar  
  Step2: Move block with index 7    // Place left half of the red ring  
  Step3: Move block with index 8    // Place right half of the red ring  
  Step4: Move block with index 9    // Place top yellow bar
}
